WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.200 --> 00:00:03.920
This is Captain Hoffman.

2
00:00:04.240 --> 00:00:05.600
Reporting for duty. Commander.

3
00:00:05.800 --> 00:00:08.640
Allow me to introduce Criminal Inspector
Forster from the Gestapo.

4
00:00:08.880 --> 00:00:12.440
Your log book. This is where
your heroic story will be recorded.

5
00:00:13.920 --> 00:00:16.440
- Pleased to meet you.
- Likewise.

6
00:00:16.760 --> 00:00:18.280
- You're French?
- No. German.

7
00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:20.600
They say you're sailing tomorrow.

8
00:00:20.920 --> 00:00:23.160
I have to go.
If not. I'll be court-martialed.

9
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.520
Shortly before 10:00 p.m.. a woman
will show up. Give her that.

10
00:00:26.720 --> 00:00:28.600
I am supposed to give you something.
From Frank.

11
00:00:28.680 --> 00:00:30.040
He sent me. I'm his sister.

12
00:00:30.120 --> 00:00:31.640
You've got something for me?

13
00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:34.240
You've got something for me!
Give it to me!

14
00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:35.400
Police!

15
00:00:37.600 --> 00:00:38.920
Out there we're on our own.

16
00:00:39.080 --> 00:00:43.120
There's only one way we will prevail.
Together!

17
00:00:44.720 --> 00:00:47.360
- Take her out. First Watch Officer.
- Harbor stations!

18
00:00:49.840 --> 00:00:52.720
- Would you come with me. please?
- Why?

19
00:00:54.000 --> 00:01:00.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

20
00:01:05.960 --> 00:01:10.000
The woman got caught with this
on her last night. Black market morphine.

21
00:01:12.320 --> 00:01:14.360
First question: Is she buying or selling?

22
00:01:15.960 --> 00:01:17.360
Please translate my question.

23
00:01:20.200 --> 00:01:22.400
The morphine. Are you buying or selling?

24
00:01:30.520 --> 00:01:34.160
Second question:
Small bottle. small offense.

25
00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:36.960
Why shoot a police officer because
of something so trivial?

26
00:01:37.080 --> 00:01:38.640
And where did she get the gun from?

27
00:01:39.760 --> 00:01:42.560
Why did you shoot a police officer?
Where did you get the gun from?

28
00:01:47.880 --> 00:01:51.560
Duval's certain that there
was someone else present. A woman.

29
00:01:52.280 --> 00:01:53.840
Ask her. who else was there.

30
00:02:00.360 --> 00:02:02.920
You've been seen with someone.

31
00:02:03.880 --> 00:02:05.040
Who was this?

32
00:02:13.880 --> 00:02:15.360
Ask her again.

33
00:02:22.200 --> 00:02:23.800
Who was this?

34
00:02:29.360 --> 00:02:33.520
You got me into deep shit.
You fucked everything up!

35
00:02:37.880 --> 00:02:38.880
What did she say?

36
00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:43.920
They'll be coming!

37
00:02:44.320 --> 00:02:46.000
Until they have what they want!

38
00:02:47.080 --> 00:02:47.960
Bitch!

39
00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:49.880
Excuse me. please.

40
00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:07.280
Are you alright. Miss Strasser?

41
00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:12.360
What did she say?

42
00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:15.600
Viendront... that's a declination
of venir... to come?

43
00:03:19.040 --> 00:03:20.440
They'll be coming... until they...

44
00:03:21.840 --> 00:03:23.360
have what they want.

45
00:03:24.960 --> 00:03:25.880
Really?

46
00:03:26.240 --> 00:03:29.840
The morphine. did she have it on her
when she got arrested?

47
00:03:30.440 --> 00:03:31.320
Why?

48
00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:34.040
Because I'd like to understand.

49
00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:38.040
She bought it from somebody
or she was trying to sell it.

50
00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:40.080
That's at least what Duval thinks.

51
00:03:40.920 --> 00:03:44.720
We'll find out. There's always a trail.
And she'll talk.

52
00:03:45.320 --> 00:03:46.320
You think?

53
00:03:46.840 --> 00:03:48.520
No. I know.

54
00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:36.800
Sir.

55
00:05:36.880 --> 00:05:38.000
Any radio messages?

56
00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:39.840
Not yet. Sir.

57
00:05:40.560 --> 00:05:43.240
I hope you had enough time
to say good-bye to your sister?

58
00:05:45.280 --> 00:05:46.160
Good.

59
00:05:46.800 --> 00:05:48.000
Well...

60
00:05:54.280 --> 00:05:55.320
Gentlemen!

61
00:05:55.960 --> 00:05:57.200
Strelitz. position?

62
00:05:57.840 --> 00:06:00.960
210 miles north-east of La Coruna.
Course two-eight-zero.

63
00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:02.360
Still nothing from Lorient?

64
00:06:05.600 --> 00:06:06.880
Time for another drill.

65
00:06:08.080 --> 00:06:11.280
Corvette. zero three five.
two thousand four hundred yards.

66
00:06:11.400 --> 00:06:12.680
angle-on-the-bow. port two zero.

67
00:06:12.960 --> 00:06:15.160
Sir. with all due respect.
the men have...

68
00:06:15.240 --> 00:06:16.960
Speed 18 knots.

69
00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:17.880
Target course?

70
00:06:17.960 --> 00:06:19.600
One-five-five. Sir.

71
00:06:19.720 --> 00:06:21.800
Course recommendation
for counter-attack two-five-three.

72
00:06:21.880 --> 00:06:23.080
Make ready tubes one and two.

73
00:06:23.840 --> 00:06:25.080
Make ready tubes one and two.

74
00:06:25.800 --> 00:06:26.920
Not again!

75
00:06:27.200 --> 00:06:28.600
Come on. assholes! Get up!

76
00:06:28.960 --> 00:06:31.200
Put the bunks away. hurry up!

77
00:06:31.280 --> 00:06:32.840
Get going. you lazy bastards.

78
00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:33.880
Rig ship for dive. Chief!

79
00:06:33.960 --> 00:06:34.960
Rig ship for dive!

80
00:06:35.040 --> 00:06:35.960
Rig ship for dive!

81
00:06:41.560 --> 00:06:44.400
Flood tubes one and two. Go. go. go!

82
00:06:44.520 --> 00:06:45.320
Matthias. let's go!

83
00:06:48.280 --> 00:06:49.120
Coming down.

84
00:06:49.760 --> 00:06:50.840
Go. go. go. go!

85
00:06:51.960 --> 00:06:53.560
- Conning tower hatch closed.
- Rig buoyancy vents.

86
00:06:53.640 --> 00:06:54.520
Aft buoyancy vent rigged.

87
00:06:54.600 --> 00:06:55.800
Both central buoyancy vents rigged.

88
00:06:55.880 --> 00:06:56.920
All buoyancy vents rigged.

89
00:06:56.960 --> 00:06:57.840
Cycle the vents.

90
00:07:03.800 --> 00:07:05.160
- Number one tube flooded.
- Good!

91
00:07:05.240 --> 00:07:06.440
Number two tube flooded!

92
00:07:06.560 --> 00:07:08.240
Open the outer doors on tubes one and two.

93
00:07:11.960 --> 00:07:13.880
The ninth drill in 10 hours!

94
00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:15.640
One can't expect to be able
to do something in war

95
00:07:15.720 --> 00:07:16.960
that one hasn't learnt in peacetime!

96
00:07:17.080 --> 00:07:18.920
What the fuck are you talking about?

97
00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:21.320
- Forget it.
- Shut the fuck up then.

98
00:07:23.120 --> 00:07:24.320
Outer door number two tube is open!

99
00:07:24.400 --> 00:07:25.880
Outer door number one tube is open!

100
00:07:26.160 --> 00:07:27.000
Good!

101
00:07:27.080 --> 00:07:28.440
Tubes one. two ready.

102
00:07:30.000 --> 00:07:31.840
Prepare one torpedo for reloading.

103
00:07:32.080 --> 00:07:33.240
Best time so far?

104
00:07:33.760 --> 00:07:34.600
Four minutes 20. Sir.

105
00:07:34.680 --> 00:07:36.000
We can do better. right?

106
00:07:37.760 --> 00:07:39.000
Periscope depth!

107
00:07:39.160 --> 00:07:41.640
Fifteen degrees down on the bow planes.
Zero degrees on the stern planes.

108
00:07:41.880 --> 00:07:43.400
Prepare one torpedo for reloading.

109
00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:47.200
Fuck! For the third time! Let's show
the old sweat! Come on. let's go!

110
00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:51.440
Okay. now lift it!

111
00:07:51.560 --> 00:07:53.760
Pull! Pull!

112
00:07:53.920 --> 00:07:55.600
Let's do something different. gentlemen.

113
00:07:57.000 --> 00:07:58.960
Fifteen degrees down
on the bow planes and keep it!

114
00:07:59.400 --> 00:08:01.880
<i>Muller.
keep bow planes 15 degrees down!</i>

115
00:08:02.240 --> 00:08:03.560
Chief. hold periscope depth!

116
00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:09.240
Bow planes jamming 15 degrees down!

117
00:08:09.440 --> 00:08:13.120
E-engines half speed. blow cell five!
All hands astern!

118
00:08:13.240 --> 00:08:15.000
All hands astern!

119
00:08:18.640 --> 00:08:19.720
Faster. faster. faster!

120
00:08:20.240 --> 00:08:21.120
Go. go. go!

121
00:08:21.200 --> 00:08:23.520
Come on! Faster. you bloody slowcoaches!

122
00:08:25.800 --> 00:08:27.440
What the heck are they doing now?

123
00:08:28.200 --> 00:08:29.760
- What's the time?
- I don't know!

124
00:08:29.840 --> 00:08:31.320
I bet we make it below four!

125
00:08:31.400 --> 00:08:32.920
Just to show this slave driver!

126
00:08:33.360 --> 00:08:34.440
I'm fine with below 4:20!

127
00:08:34.560 --> 00:08:36.160
Below four!
Crate of beer in the next harbor!

128
00:08:36.240 --> 00:08:37.240
Bet's on!

129
00:08:38.760 --> 00:08:43.200
Damn it! Pull it back!
Go! Back down. front up!

130
00:08:50.960 --> 00:08:52.000
We're too deep!

131
00:08:52.240 --> 00:08:53.280
One meter up!

132
00:08:53.360 --> 00:08:54.920
Twenty degrees up on the stern planes.

133
00:08:57.240 --> 00:08:58.600
<i>Stay calm. Muller.</i>

134
00:08:59.520 --> 00:09:00.360
Stay calm.

135
00:09:12.760 --> 00:09:13.800
Boat has been oscillated.

136
00:09:15.440 --> 00:09:17.440
She's dancing on tiptoes.
like a ballerina!

137
00:09:19.520 --> 00:09:21.240
Come on. Matthias. let's go.

138
00:09:23.240 --> 00:09:24.080
Secure it!

139
00:09:24.440 --> 00:09:25.280
Secured!

140
00:09:25.600 --> 00:09:26.400
- Secured!
- Secured!

141
00:09:26.840 --> 00:09:28.760
The torpedo is. but the CO isn't!

142
00:09:29.920 --> 00:09:31.160
Torpedo ready to reload. Sir.

143
00:09:32.840 --> 00:09:34.080
3:58. gentlemen.

144
00:09:34.200 --> 00:09:35.160
Well done. Muller.

145
00:09:36.040 --> 00:09:38.160
- Sir.
- You all did a good job.

146
00:09:38.240 --> 00:09:40.080
God damn it. that was hard work!

147
00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:44.120
You should not take the name
of the Lord thy God in vain! Asshole!

148
00:09:44.880 --> 00:09:46.240
You owe me a crate of beer.

149
00:09:48.600 --> 00:09:50.320
Take it down again.

150
00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:52.080
Rig for surface.

151
00:09:52.560 --> 00:09:53.440
Sir?

152
00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:55.320
Radio message from Lorient!

153
00:10:11.840 --> 00:10:14.960
Proceed to naval square
Bruno Fritz seven one!

154
00:10:16.080 --> 00:10:18.760
Report our position naval square
Bruno Fritz five eight

155
00:10:18.840 --> 00:10:19.720
to submarine command.

156
00:10:19.800 --> 00:10:20.880
Aye. Sir.

157
00:10:24.440 --> 00:10:26.320
Time required until reaching
the theater of operations?

158
00:10:30.920 --> 00:10:32.560
Twelve hours at full speed. Sir.

159
00:10:32.960 --> 00:10:34.600
Enough time for some more drills.

160
00:10:44.440 --> 00:10:47.560
The purpose of a drill is
to test the men under pressure.

161
00:10:48.920 --> 00:10:50.440
Without pressure. there's no test.

162
00:10:51.320 --> 00:10:52.240
But I think that...

163
00:10:53.080 --> 00:10:54.200
you know this. First Watch Officer.

164
00:10:54.400 --> 00:10:55.240
Right?

165
00:11:02.440 --> 00:11:04.000
Gentlemen.
this is the Captain speaking.

166
00:11:04.600 --> 00:11:08.280
We are going on intercept course
to an Allied Convoy heading south-west.

167
00:11:08.360 --> 00:11:09.200
Yeah!

168
00:11:09.280 --> 00:11:10.960
I repeat: We're going on intercept course.

169
00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:11.960
Full speed ahead.

170
00:11:12.160 --> 00:11:13.280
Full speed ahead.

171
00:11:15.400 --> 00:11:16.800
You'll take over. First Watch Officer.

172
00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:27.000
Well.

173
00:11:27.960 --> 00:11:29.760
Maybe he's like his father after all.

174
00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:34.040
His father was a Captain.
not a slave driver.

175
00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:38.360
We'll find out soon enough
how he is under pressure.

176
00:14:17.040 --> 00:14:18.360
What are you doing here. Emile?

177
00:14:19.360 --> 00:14:22.360
Wrong question.
What is she doing in prison?

178
00:14:23.440 --> 00:14:24.280
Who?

179
00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:27.240
Who? Jacqueline.

180
00:14:30.800 --> 00:14:32.120
Somebody tipped the police off.

181
00:14:33.200 --> 00:14:34.160
The church...

182
00:14:35.440 --> 00:14:36.960
only we knew about it...

183
00:14:37.760 --> 00:14:39.160
the U-boat man...

184
00:14:39.520 --> 00:14:40.320
and you.

185
00:14:41.080 --> 00:14:42.000
Nobody else.

186
00:14:43.600 --> 00:14:44.600
He must have talked.

187
00:14:45.160 --> 00:14:46.320
Frank Strasser?

188
00:14:48.560 --> 00:14:50.440
They certainly found the morphine on her.

189
00:14:53.280 --> 00:14:56.240
What do you think? How long will it take
the Germans to find out about you?

190
00:14:57.440 --> 00:14:58.560
She stole it.

191
00:15:00.080 --> 00:15:02.440
- No idea. how. It's as simple as that.
- I need more.

192
00:15:03.560 --> 00:15:05.280
- Everything you got.
- No.

193
00:15:05.600 --> 00:15:07.520
Tell Miss Monroe it's over.

194
00:15:08.800 --> 00:15:09.840
No more morphine.

195
00:15:11.800 --> 00:15:13.400
And now get out of my office.

196
00:15:16.680 --> 00:15:19.040
The patient in room 17.
you have to change...

197
00:15:57.960 --> 00:15:58.920
Hello.

198
00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:01.000
Hello.

199
00:16:11.840 --> 00:16:14.000
- Who are you?
- My name is Simone.

200
00:16:15.120 --> 00:16:16.360
I'm his sister.

201
00:16:18.280 --> 00:16:19.800
What's your name?

202
00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:21.280
Nathalie.

203
00:16:21.440 --> 00:16:22.400
You two are together?

204
00:16:24.840 --> 00:16:25.840
He didn't tell me.

205
00:16:26.040 --> 00:16:27.080
Where is Frank?

206
00:16:28.160 --> 00:16:31.880
Gone to sea. He had no choice.
Orders.

207
00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:39.040
Last night he sent me to meet a woman.
To make an exchange.

208
00:16:39.840 --> 00:16:41.000
I don't understand why.

209
00:16:41.560 --> 00:16:42.800
Please. leave.

210
00:16:43.240 --> 00:16:44.960
I think it's about morphine.

211
00:16:45.760 --> 00:16:48.240
- Is Frank an addict?
- Leave! Please!

212
00:16:48.520 --> 00:16:51.200
You have to help me!
I need to understand.

213
00:16:51.520 --> 00:16:53.040
- Yes. please?
- Are you the new girl?

214
00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:54.960
- Frank is in danger.
- New girl?

215
00:16:55.400 --> 00:16:56.440
What can I get you. mister?

216
00:16:56.880 --> 00:16:58.720
- You have to help me...
- Will you join me in my room?

217
00:16:58.840 --> 00:17:00.960
- Darling. what's going on here?
- You've got great lips.

218
00:17:01.080 --> 00:17:02.440
Leave me alone!

219
00:17:02.560 --> 00:17:03.840
What's wrong with you?

220
00:17:03.920 --> 00:17:06.040
- Come with me to the room.
- She's mine!

221
00:17:07.560 --> 00:17:09.160
French slut!

222
00:17:51.760 --> 00:17:53.160
Monsieur Duval?

223
00:19:17.520 --> 00:19:19.000
That's all I could get.

224
00:19:22.160 --> 00:19:23.360
What if she talks?

225
00:19:25.400 --> 00:19:27.240
She will talk at some point. Even her.

226
00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:30.840
You can leave. But Luc. Marc.
Claude and me... our families are here.

227
00:20:28.800 --> 00:20:31.160
Still not talking.

228
00:20:33.280 --> 00:20:35.880
Tell us about the morphine
and it all stops.

229
00:20:50.960 --> 00:20:54.840
You're not a drug addict either.
No needle marks...

230
00:21:10.640 --> 00:21:12.240
International Brigades?

231
00:22:09.560 --> 00:22:11.200
Scream and you're dead!

232
00:22:11.880 --> 00:22:12.960
Not one word!

233
00:22:13.320 --> 00:22:14.200
Sit down!

234
00:26:05.440 --> 00:26:06.840
Commander!

235
00:26:07.360 --> 00:26:12.360
Sorry for interrupting your morning walk.
but your presence is required.

236
00:26:12.680 --> 00:26:14.360
Top secret orders from Berlin.

237
00:26:26.560 --> 00:26:27.880
Good morning. Miss Strasser.

238
00:26:32.280 --> 00:26:33.320
Good morning.

239
00:26:33.920 --> 00:26:35.840
That was a rather unfortunate situation.

240
00:26:36.360 --> 00:26:39.160
The prisoner was more forthright
than I'd expected.

241
00:26:40.000 --> 00:26:41.360
She's a communist.

242
00:26:41.960 --> 00:26:43.120
What? A communist?

243
00:26:43.240 --> 00:26:45.560
It's unlikely she acted alone.
But whoever helped her.

244
00:26:45.920 --> 00:26:48.120
I'll hunt them down.

245
00:26:48.600 --> 00:26:51.600
It's my job to protect La Rochelle
from these elements.

246
00:26:52.240 --> 00:26:55.000
These are the people we're at war with.
They are enemies of the Reich.

247
00:26:55.920 --> 00:26:58.960
But they'll pay with their lives.
Rest assured.

248
00:27:02.000 --> 00:27:03.840
Is there something else bothering you?

249
00:27:05.000 --> 00:27:07.000
Is it because of your brother? Frank?

250
00:27:08.360 --> 00:27:10.960
You'd just arrived when he was ordered
to sail out. Of course...

251
00:27:11.680 --> 00:27:13.040
that's not easy for you.

252
00:27:14.400 --> 00:27:18.160
My brother.
my brother means a lot to me...

253
00:27:18.320 --> 00:27:19.520
Criminal Inspector Forster...

254
00:27:19.760 --> 00:27:21.440
Commander Gluck will see you now.

255
00:27:21.960 --> 00:27:22.960
I'm coming.

256
00:27:25.600 --> 00:27:26.920
You'll excuse me?

257
00:27:33.160 --> 00:27:34.200
A secret mission?

258
00:27:34.560 --> 00:27:36.760
Yes. a secret non-combat mission.

259
00:27:37.200 --> 00:27:38.960
This comes directly from Goebbels' office.

260
00:27:39.520 --> 00:27:42.400
They only need me for assigning a boat
to this mission.

261
00:27:42.720 --> 00:27:43.560
Propaganda?

262
00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:48.400
That's why you're here. A political
decision requires a political mind.

263
00:27:48.640 --> 00:27:53.960
No offense. Our duty should be
to sink Allied ships.

264
00:27:54.240 --> 00:27:58.960
Starving out a nation
of 60 million requires every single boat.

265
00:28:00.800 --> 00:28:03.400
Here's the list of operational boats
